Mauritius Commercial Bank, Nation’s Largest, Up Most in 10 Days

-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 
2011-03-21T09:26:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-21/mauritius-commercial-bank-nation-s-largest-up-most-in-10-days.html
Mauritius Commercial Bank, the
country’s largest lender by market value, rose the most in 10
days.  The stock advanced 3 rupees, or 1.86 percent, to 164
rupees, the biggest intraday rise since March 11, as of 12:20
p.m in Mauritius. The stock has fallen from 171 rupees this
month.  “Local support for the stock was waiting for the right
time to get back,” Kishen Nadassen, a senior research analyst
at CIM Stockbrokers Ltd. in Mauritius, said in a phone
interview. “They are now in at an interesting price.”  To contact the reporter on this story: Kamlesh Bhuckory in Port
Louis via Johannesburg at 
 gbell16@bloomberg.net  